A woman in her late 60s was murdered in the Cromdale area this morning, February 28. Albert Gryvenstein of Bossies Community Justice confirmed the incident to Lowvelder and said a suspect is already being questioned. ALSO READ: Silulumanzi in process of repairing burst pipe in Mbombela Gryvenstein was called out to the scene at about 04:00. The woman’s identity is known to the newspaper, but it is being withheld as her next of kin have not yet been notified. This is a developing story.